[size=140][b]Adding Indent to Text[/b][/size]
[color=#aeaeae][size=20][u]                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           [/u][/size][/color]

  Indentation sometimes needed when you want to write text with "clutter-free" looking. All you need is add 2x Em Space on beginning of paragraph. Em space is accessible by adding [b]&#8195;[/b] or [b]&emsp;[/b] on your HTML document.

  Here is technical info about em space:
[code]Name			:	Em Space
Unicode Version		:	1.1 (June 1993)
Block			:	General Punctuation, U+2000 - U+206F
Plane			:	Basic Multilingual Plane, U+0000 - U+FFFF
Script			:	Code for undetermined script (Zyyy)
Category		:	Space Separator (Zs)
Bidirectional Class	:	White Space (WS)
Combining Class		:	Not Reordered (0)
Character is Mirrored	:	No
HTML Entity		:	&#8195;
				&#x2003;
				&emsp;
UTF-8 Encoding		:	0xE2 0x80 0x83
UTF-16 Encoding		:	0x2003
UTF-32 Encoding		:	0x00002003
Decomposition		:	(U+0020)[/code]
  To add em space manually from keyboard, tap [b]Alt[/b], followed by type [b]8195[/b] from your numpad. If your keyboard does not have numpad, you need to open [url=https://www.compart.com/en/unicode/U+2003]this site [img]https://id.wikipedia.org/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/external-link-ltr-icon.svg?b4b84[/img][/url] to helps you copying em space.

[quote][size=120][b]Pro tip:[/b][/size]
Use this method if you want to use it to comment, blog post, and forum thread. Otherwise, you can still use &emsp; on messages[/quote]

